[{"question":"What do you want to say?","answer":"First thing I want to say is I\u0027m loathe to be here frankly.","docId":"120729pmt","qSentId":37,"aSentId":38},{"question":"So, really, what\u0027s the real reason?","answer":"On --","docId":"120729pmt","qSentId":131,"aSentId":132},{"question":"What are we afraid of?","answer":"Here\u0027s what I see just a fundamental flaw in the American gun culture.","docId":"120729pmt","qSentId":139,"aSentId":140},{"question":"Did you expect the impact of both the massacre in Columbine and your movie to have more effect than it\u0027s had?","answer":"Well, this is the continuing problem I have with all my movies.","docId":"120729pmt","qSentId":208,"aSentId":209},{"question":"And do you see any link between that and these sorts of incidents?","answer":"No.","docId":"120729pmt","qSentId":260,"aSentId":261},{"question":"Makes it easier, though, doesn\u0027t it?","answer":"Not really.","docId":"120729pmt","qSentId":265,"aSentId":266},{"question":"How do you deal with the constitutional divide that America has over how that is interpreted?","answer":"OK.","docId":"120729pmt","qSentId":273,"aSentId":274},{"question":"Why is that?","answer":"I guess they\u0027re afraid to.","docId":"120729pmt","qSentId":336,"aSentId":337},{"question":"That is why America is seeing such an escalation in its gun ownership, isn\u0027t it?","answer":"It\u0027s -- no, I think it -- actually, it\u0027s -- it\u0027s more because we\u0027re easy -- we\u0027re easily scared than other people in other countries.","docId":"120729pmt","qSentId":366,"aSentId":367},{"question":"What is it about us that we are so cruel to each other?","answer":"I think it -- it\u0027s a fascinating question and I think it\u0027s one that many Americans are wrestling with.","docId":"120729pmt","qSentId":400,"aSentId":401},{"question":"We\u0027re -- we\u0027re -- you know, where are you going to draw the line here with this?","answer":"Well, this is the point, isn\u0027t it.","docId":"120729pmt","qSentId":449,"aSentId":450},{"question":"Who do you think is going to come into your house?","answer":"On this point, a clear example, to me, of the kind of thing you\u0027re talking about is the Trayvon Martin case, where George Zimmerman, if he hadn\u0027t been carrying a gun, indisputably Trayvon Martin would still be alive.","docId":"120729pmt","qSentId":486,"aSentId":487},{"question":"Doesn\u0027t Trayvon Martin actually have the right to kill George Zimmerman if George Zimmerman is stalking him and -- and the police have told him not to stalk him?","answer":"There is an irony that it\u0027s George Zimmerman using Florida\u0027s \"stand your ground\" defense when, in fact, as you say, you could equally argue that Trayvon Martin may well have been doing the same thing.","docId":"120729pmt","qSentId":497,"aSentId":498},{"question":"Is it time that America just woke up and dealt properly with mental health generally?","answer":"Absolutely.","docId":"120729pmt","qSentId":533,"aSentId":534},{"question":"When you knew that picture was coming out, how did you feel?","answer":"Not too good.","docId":"120729pmt","qSentId":604,"aSentId":605},{"question":"What is that feeling like?","answer":"HELPS: Like the worst in the world, you know, like the lowest of the low.","docId":"120729pmt","qSentId":606,"aSentId":607},{"question":"How did you brace yourself for that?","answer":"You know, I think my mom has always been obviously how all moms are.","docId":"120729pmt","qSentId":612,"aSentId":613}]